-- Morgan Stanley reports quarterly share loss
-- 
-- Wed Dec 17, 2008 8:19am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/12/17/us-morgan-idUSTRE4BG3OG20081217

 

 (Reuters) - Morgan Stanley reported on Wednesday a fourth quarter loss per share of $2.24 from continuing operations. 

 Highlights: * Q4 loss per share $2.34 * Q4 revenue $2 billion * Q4 non-interest expenses of $5.2 billion, including non-cash charges of $725 million * Qtrly institutional securities posted a pre-tax loss of $2.1 billion * Says targeting additional $2 billion in cost savings including annualized effect of headcount reductions and additional non-compensation expense savings * Qtrly fixed income sales and trading net losses were $1.2 billion * Qtrly equity sales and trading net revenues of $1.7 billion * Says launching a retail banking group and recruiting cece sutton and jonathan witter to lead the business * Qtrly investment losses were $1.8 billion * Q4 asset management posted a pre-tax loss of $1,215 million * Qtrly total client assets of $546 billion declined $212 billion, or 28 percent * Says john mack, chairman and CEO, and co-presidents walid chammah and james gorman have forgone a bonus for 2008 * Q4 assets under management or supervision at November 30, 2008 of $399 billion * Says 2008 year-end compensation for the 14 members of the firm's operating committee is down an average of 75 percent * Says 2008 year-end compensation for the 35 members of the management committee is down an average of 65 percent versus last year * Says excluding financial advisor compensation, the firm's bonus pool is down about 50 percent for 2008 * Says compensation-to-net revenue ratio for 2008 was 49.7 percent * Says board approved a change in the firm's fiscal year end from November 30 to December 31 of each year * Says board of directors declared a $0.27 quarterly dividend per common share * Says total capital as of November 30, 2008 was $192.3 billion * Reuters Estimates Q4 earnings per share view $-0.33, revenue view $3,958.88 million